text=PmWiki uses a number of directives to specify page titles, descriptions, page keywords, and control the display of various components.%0a%0a:[@(:title text:)@]: Sets a page's title to be something other than the page's name.  The title text can contain apostrophes and other special characters.%0a%0a:[@(:keywords word1, word2, ...:)@]:Identifies keywords associated with the page.  These are not displayed anywhere, but are useful to help search engines locate the page.  (Essentially, this generates a [@%3cmeta name='keywords' content='...' />@] element in the output.)%0a%0a:[@(:description text:)@]:Descriptive text associated with the page.  (Generates a [@%3cmeta name='description' content='...' />@] element in the page output.)%0a%0a:[@(:redirect PageName:)@]:Redirects the browser to another page, along with a redirect message.  For security reasons this only redirects to other pages within the wiki and does not redirect to external urls.%0a%0a:[@(:noheader:)@]:%0a:[@(:nofooter:)@]: %0a:[@(:notitle:)@]:%0a:[@(:noleft:)@]:%0a: :If supported by the [[skin(s)]], turns off the header, footer, title area, or left sidebar.%0a%0a:[@(:nogroupheader:)@]:%0a:[@(:nogroupfooter:)@]:%0a: :Turns off any groupheader or groupfooter for the page.  (See [[GroupHeaders]].)%0a%0a:[@(:linkwikiwords:), (:nolinkwikiwords:)@]:%0a:[@(:spacewikiwords:), (:nospacewikiwords:)@]:%0a: :Enables/disables WikiWord links and automatic spacing of WikiWords in text.%0a%0a%25trail%25%3c%3c|[[DocumentationIndex]]|>>
